properties.areaDesc: Santa Barbara County South Coast; Santa Barbara County Mountains
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 24 at 9:38AM PST until January 25 at 3:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northeast winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 mph.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County South Coast and Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 3 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strongest winds will be between Refugio
Beach and the Gaviota tunnel on Highway 101 as well as the
western Santa Ynez Range.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 AM PST SATURDAY
